<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Fascinated by the marvelous spectacle that seemed to be performed <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="in her honor"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(为了表示对她的敬意)</code></b>, for she was the only person watching it, Fermina Daza did not notice when the passengers for the return trip began to come on board.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>When it was over, however, she <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="felt empty"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(感到心里空荡荡的)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>The party was over: among them she saw many faces she knew, some of them friends who until a short while ago had <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="attended"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(陪同)</code></b> her in her grief, and she rushed to take refuge in her cabin.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>But Florentino Ariza <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="pursued the discussion to its end"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(继续讨论到底)</code></b>, and only then did he ask the question that the Captain thought was the prelude to a solution.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Besides, many times in the history of the river the yellow plague <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="flag had been flown"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(升起旗帜)</code></b> in order to evade taxes, or to avoid picking up an undesirable passenger, or to elude inopportune inspections.</p>
  </li>
